{"add":{"doc":{"id":"71207cb0e12e57c9915d7ebad2a2f0405fdf76651d421dc3bbd3ac80d70e4873","url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/fe/Caslon-schriftmusterblatt.jpeg/350px-Caslon-schriftmusterblatt.jpeg","previous":[],"after":["In the examination of individual scripts, the study of writing systems has developed along partially independent lines. Thus, the terminology employed differs somewhat from field to field.","The generic term text refers to an instance of written material. The act of composing and recording a text may be referred to as writing, and the act of viewing and interpreting the text as reading. Orthography refers to the method and rules of observed writing structure (literal meaning, \"correct writing\"), and particularly for alphabetic systems, includes the concept of spelling."]}}}